  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "gegl04 security update",
      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for gegl04 is now available for openEuler-24.03-LTS,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP1,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP2,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP3,openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "GEGL provides infrastructure to do demand based cached non destructive image editing on larger than RAM buffers. Through babl, it provides support for a wide range of color models and pixel storage formats for input and output.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n(CVE-2026-2049)\n\n(CVE-2026-2050)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for gegl04 is now available for openEuler-24.03-LTS,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP1,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP2,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP3,openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of critical. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Critical",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "gegl04",
